               <msContents>
                  <summary>This text preserves the upper right-hand quarter of a tax list containing payers of the andrismos or poll tax. The payers who still survive on the papyrus are sack weavers and a priest who have paid the tax in kind at the rate of one or three sacks. The left-hand side presumably listed the name of the payers.</summary>
